Note:
==============================================================================
CASCADE - CSS Cascade Resolution + Computed-Style Builder
==============================================================================

Implements the CSS cascade and computed-style assembly per CSS Cascade
and Inheritance Level 5 (https://www.w3.org/TR/css-cascade-5/).

Resolution order (CSS Cascade 5 section 6):

  1. Origin and importance
        - !important user-agent
        - !important user
        - !important author
        - animations
        - author normal
        - user normal
        - user-agent normal
        - transitions
  2. Specificity (a, b, c, d): higher wins
  3. Source order: later wins

Inherited-property resolution: if a property is inherited and the
element has no declared value, take the parent's computed value;
otherwise use the property's initial value.

Custom-property (--name) handling: cascade in their own substitution
phase, then substitute via var(--name, fallback) in later property
values.

Records:

  MatchedDeclaration (48 bytes):
    off  0  property name      (NUL-terminated)
    off  8  value string       (NUL-terminated)
    off 16  important          0 or 1
    off 24  origin             ORIGIN_*
    off 32  specificity ptr    (24-byte buffer from selector.specificity)
    off 40  source_order       integer

  ComputedStyle (16 bytes):
    off  0  properties dict    (Dictionary[name -> value string])
    off  8  source             (element pointer or 0)

The cascade builds a list of MatchedDeclarations for the element by
walking the stylesheet rules and checking selector matches, then sorts
the list by (importance, origin, specificity, source-order), then
materializes the final ComputedStyle by overlaying declarations in
sorted order.

References:
  - CSS Cascade 5:        https://www.w3.org/TR/css-cascade-5/
  - CSS Selectors 4 spec: https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-4/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/style/selector.runa" as Sel
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/style/style_rule.runa" as Rule
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/style/property.runa" as Prop
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/markup/element.runa" as Elem
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/markup/selector.runa" as MS

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant ORIGIN_USER_AGENT as Integer is 0
Constant ORIGIN_USER as Integer is 1
Constant ORIGIN_AUTHOR as Integer is 2
Constant ORIGIN_ANIMATION as Integer is 3
Constant ORIGIN_TRANSITION as Integer is 4

Constant MATCHED_SIZE as Integer is 48
Constant MATCHED_OFF_NAME as Integer is 0
Constant MATCHED_OFF_VALUE as Integer is 8
Constant MATCHED_OFF_IMPORTANT as Integer is 16
Constant MATCHED_OFF_ORIGIN as Integer is 24
Constant MATCHED_OFF_SPEC as Integer is 32
Constant MATCHED_OFF_ORDER as Integer is 40

Constant COMPUTED_SIZE as Integer is 16
Constant COMPUTED_OFF_PROPS as Integer is 0
Constant COMPUTED_OFF_SOURCE as Integer is 8

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MATCHED DECLARATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a MatchedDeclaration record capturing a declaration's text,
importance flag, origin, specificity, and source-order index.  These
records are sorted by the cascade before being applied to the computed
style.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.allocate 48 bytes; write all six slots.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller owns specificity buffer; name/value strings are borrowed.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "matched_create" takes name as Integer, value as Integer, important as Integer, origin as Integer, spec as Integer, order as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with MATCHED_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, MATCHED_OFF_NAME, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, MATCHED_OFF_VALUE, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, MATCHED_OFF_IMPORTANT, important
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, MATCHED_OFF_ORIGIN, origin
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, MATCHED_OFF_SPEC, spec
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, MATCHED_OFF_ORDER, order
    Return record
End Process

Process called "matched_destroy" takes m as Integer returns Integer:
    If m is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let spec be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, MATCHED_OFF_SPEC
    If spec is not equal to 0:
        proc specificity_destroy from Sel with spec
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with m
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CASCADE ORDERING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compare two MatchedDeclarations by the cascade order defined in CSS
Cascade Level 5 section 6.  Returns -1 if A precedes B (A loses), 1 if
A succeeds B (A wins), 0 if equal.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Origin weight: important flips author/user origins to high-priority
slots.  Specifically the comparison uses an "effective importance"
score: 0 for normal author/user/user-agent, 100 for !important
user-agent, 200 for !important user, 300 for !important author, 50 for
animations, 25 for transitions.  Then compare specificity: a > a, b > b,
c > c.  Then source order: later wins.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Pure function; no allocation.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "matched_effective_priority" takes m as Integer returns Integer:
    Let important be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, MATCHED_OFF_IMPORTANT
    Let origin be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, MATCHED_OFF_ORIGIN
    If important is equal to 1:
        If origin is equal to ORIGIN_USER_AGENT:
            Return 100
        End If
        If origin is equal to ORIGIN_USER:
            Return 200
        End If
        If origin is equal to ORIGIN_AUTHOR:
            Return 300
        End If
    End If
    If origin is equal to ORIGIN_TRANSITION:
        Return 25
    End If
    If origin is equal to ORIGIN_ANIMATION:
        Return 50
    End If
    If origin is equal to ORIGIN_USER_AGENT:
        Return 1
    End If
    If origin is equal to ORIGIN_USER:
        Return 2
    End If
    Return 3
End Process

Process called "matched_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let pa be proc matched_effective_priority with a
    Let pb be proc matched_effective_priority with b
    If pa is less than pb:
        Return -1
    End If
    If pa is greater than pb:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let sa be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, MATCHED_OFF_SPEC
    Let sb be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, MATCHED_OFF_SPEC
    If sa is not equal to 0:
        If sb is not equal to 0:
            Let cmp be proc specificity_compare from Sel with sa, sb
            If cmp is not equal to 0:
                Return cmp
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let oa be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, MATCHED_OFF_ORDER
    Let ob be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, MATCHED_OFF_ORDER
    If oa is less than ob:
        Return -1
    End If
    If oa is greater than ob:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Insertion-sort the matched list in place using matched_compare.  Sort
is stable and O(n^2) — acceptable because per-element cascade lists are
typically small (under 100 entries).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Standard insertion-sort over the underlying List, swapping pointers via
list_set.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n^2) worst case; O(n) on near-sorted input.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Pure; no allocation beyond what list_set / list_get already use.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "matched_sort" takes matched as Integer returns Integer:
    Let n be proc list_length from List with matched
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than n:
        Let cur be proc list_get from List with matched, i
        Let j be i minus 1
        While j is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let head be proc list_get from List with matched, j
            Let cmp be proc matched_compare with head, cur
            If cmp is greater than 0:
                proc list_set from List with matched, j plus 1, head
                Set j to j minus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set j to -1
            End If
        End While
        proc list_set from List with matched, j plus 1, cur
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COLLECTION FROM STYLESHEETS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Walk a single stylesheet, matching every rule's selector against the
target element, and append a MatchedDeclaration for each declaration
in matching rules.  Source-order counter is updated and returned.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
For each entry in the stylesheet, dispatch on kind.  Rules with a list
selector are split into list members, each independently matched
against the element.  For a match, every declaration in the rule
produces a MatchedDeclaration.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(rules * matcher_cost).  For multi-piece selectors the matcher cost
dominates.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
specificity buffer is owned by the MatchedDeclaration; if the matched
list is destroyed via matched_destroy_all the buffers are released.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cascade_collect_from_sheet" takes element as Integer, sheet as Integer, origin as Integer, matched as Integer, order_start as Integer returns Integer:
    If sheet is equal to 0:
        Return order_start
    End If
    Let count be proc stylesheet_entry_count from Rule with sheet
    Let i be 0
    Let order be order_start
    While i is less than count:
        Let kind be proc stylesheet_get_kind_at from Rule with sheet, i
        Let entry be proc stylesheet_get_entry_at from Rule with sheet, i
        If kind is equal to 1:
            Let sel be proc rule_get_selector from Rule with entry
            Let decls be proc rule_get_declarations from Rule with entry
            Let m be proc selector_match from MS with element, sel
            If m is equal to 1:
                Let dcount be proc list_length from List with decls
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than dcount:
                    Let decl be proc list_get from List with decls, j
                    Let dname be proc declaration_get_name from Rule with decl
                    Let dvalue be proc declaration_get_value from Rule with decl
                    Let dimp be proc declaration_is_important from Rule with decl
                    Let spec be proc selector_specificity from Sel with sel
                    Let mr be proc matched_create with dname, dvalue, dimp, origin, spec, order
                    If mr is not equal to 0:
                        proc list_push from List with matched, mr
                    End If
                    Set order to order plus 1
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return order
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COMPUTED STYLE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a ComputedStyle record backed by a Dictionary mapping
property name -> raw value string.  The source element pointer is kept
for downstream computed-value resolution (em-relative lengths, etc).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Allocate 16 bytes; create the backing dictionary.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller owns the ComputedStyle; computed_destroy releases both record
and dictionary.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "computed_create" takes source_element as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with COMPUTED_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let props be proc create from Dict
    If props is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with record
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, COMPUTED_OFF_PROPS, props
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, COMPUTED_OFF_SOURCE, source_element
    Return record
End Process

Process called "computed_get" takes computed as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If computed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let props be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with computed, COMPUTED_OFF_PROPS
    Return proc get from Dict with props, name
End Process

Process called "computed_set" takes computed as Integer, name as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If computed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let props be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with computed, COMPUTED_OFF_PROPS
    Return proc set from Dict with props, name, value
End Process

Process called "computed_destroy" takes computed as Integer returns Integer:
    If computed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let props be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with computed, COMPUTED_OFF_PROPS
    If props is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from Dict with props
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with computed
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CASCADE APPLICATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Substitute var(--name, fallback) occurrences in a raw value string
against the custom-property dictionary.  Returns a freshly allocated
expanded string or the original pointer if no substitution was needed.
Designed for simple top-level var() references; nested var() is
handled by re-running expansion on the substituted result up to a
fixed depth to avoid infinite recursion.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Scan the value for the literal "var(--".  When found, capture the
variable name up to ',' or ')', look it up in the custom-property
dictionary, substitute its value (or the literal fallback after ',').
Loop until no further var( substrings appear or a depth ceiling is hit.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length * substitution_count).  Depth ceiling 32 prevents pathological
input.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns a caller-owned string (or the original pointer with caller
still responsible).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cascade_extract_var_name" takes text as Integer, start as Integer, out_end as Integer, out_fallback_start as Integer returns Integer:
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let i be start
    Let depth be 0
    Let fallback_start be -1
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If ch is equal to 40:
            Set depth to depth plus 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 41:
            If depth is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, i
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_fallback_start, 0, fallback_start
                Return 1
            End If
            Set depth to depth minus 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 44:
            If depth is equal to 0:
                If fallback_start is equal to -1:
                    Set fallback_start to i plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, -1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_fallback_start, 0, -1
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "cascade_substitute_vars_once" takes value as Integer, custom_props as Integer, out_changed as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_changed, 0, 0
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_changed, 0, 0
        Return value
    End If
    Let i be 0
    Let changed be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let c0 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i
        Let remaining be len minus i
        If c0 is equal to 118:
            If remaining is greater than or equal to 6:
                Let c1 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i plus 1
                Let c2 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i plus 2
                Let c3 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i plus 3
                Let c4 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i plus 4
                Let c5 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i plus 5
                If c1 is equal to 97:
                    If c2 is equal to 114:
                        If c3 is equal to 40:
                            If c4 is equal to 45:
                                If c5 is equal to 45:
                                    Let end_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
                                    Let fb_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with end_slot, 0, 0
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with fb_slot, 0, 0
                                    proc cascade_extract_var_name with value, i plus 4, end_slot, fb_slot
                                    Let close_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with end_slot, 0
                                    Let fb_start be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fb_slot, 0
                                    proc deallocate from Layout with end_slot
                                    proc deallocate from Layout with fb_slot
                                    If close_pos is greater than 0:
                                        Let name_end be close_pos
                                        If fb_start is greater than 0:
                                            Set name_end to fb_start minus 1
                                        End If
                                        Let name_sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
                                        Let k be i plus 4
                                        While k is less than name_end:
                                            Let nch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, k
                                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with name_sb, nch
                                            Set k to k plus 1
                                        End While
                                        Let var_name be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with name_sb
                                        proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with name_sb
                                        Let resolved be proc get from Dict with custom_props, var_name
                                        If resolved is equal to 0:
                                            If fb_start is greater than 0:
                                                Let fb_sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
                                                Let f be fb_start
                                                While f is less than close_pos:
                                                    Let fch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, f
                                                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with fb_sb, fch
                                                    Set f to f plus 1
                                                End While
                                                Let fallback_val be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with fb_sb
                                                proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with fb_sb
                                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, fallback_val
                                            End If
                                        Otherwise:
                                            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, resolved
                                        End If
                                        Set i to close_pos plus 1
                                        Set changed to 1
                                    Otherwise:
                                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
                                        Set i to i plus 1
                                    End If
                                Otherwise:
                                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
                                    Set i to i plus 1
                                End If
                            Otherwise:
                                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
                                Set i to i plus 1
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
                            Set i to i plus 1
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
                        Set i to i plus 1
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End If
            Otherwise:
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, c0
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_changed, 0, changed
    If changed is equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
        Return value
    End If
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Resolve `var(--name)` substitutions iteratively until stable or a
depth ceiling.  Nested var() is handled by re-substituting until no
further var( appears, capping at 32 rounds to break cycles.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Loop cascade_substitute_vars_once; halt when no change.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
At most 32 rounds * cost-of-single-pass.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns a caller-owned string (possibly the input pointer if no
substitution).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cascade_resolve_value" takes value as Integer, custom_props as Integer returns Integer:
    Let current be value
    Let depth be 0
    Let changed_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    If changed_slot is equal to 0:
        Return value
    End If
    While depth is less than 32:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with changed_slot, 0, 0
        Let next_val be proc cascade_substitute_vars_once with current, custom_props, changed_slot
        Let ch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with changed_slot, 0
        If ch is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with changed_slot
            Return current
        End If
        Set current to next_val
        Set depth to depth plus 1
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with changed_slot
    Return current
End Process

@Reasoning
Top-level cascade.  Builds the matched-declaration list from each
supplied stylesheet, sorts by cascade priority, applies in order to
fill the ComputedStyle, then layers inherited-property fallback (from
the parent element's computed style if supplied) and initial-value
fallback (from the property registry).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
1. For each stylesheet in the supplied lists, run cascade_collect_from_sheet
   tagged with its origin.
2. matched_sort.
3. Build a dictionary of custom-property declarations from the matched
   list (separating "--name" properties).
4. For every other matched declaration, var-resolve the value and
   write it into the ComputedStyle (later writers overwrite earlier
   per the sort).
5. For every property in the registry, if not present in the computed
   style and the property is inherited and the parent_computed supplies
   it, copy from parent.  Otherwise use the registry's initial value.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(stylesheets * rules * matcher_cost + matched^2 + registry).  For
typical pages all these are small.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on OOM.  Custom-properties dictionary released before return.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cascade_apply" takes element as Integer, sheets as Integer, origins as Integer, parent_computed as Integer, registry as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let matched be proc list_create from List
    If matched is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sheet_count be 0
    If sheets is not equal to 0:
        Set sheet_count to proc list_length from List with sheets
    End If
    Let i be 0
    Let order be 0
    While i is less than sheet_count:
        Let sheet be proc list_get from List with sheets, i
        Let origin be ORIGIN_AUTHOR
        If origins is not equal to 0:
            Let provided_origin be proc list_get from List with origins, i
            Set origin to provided_origin
        End If
        Set order to proc cascade_collect_from_sheet with element, sheet, origin, matched, order
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc matched_sort with matched
    Let computed be proc computed_create with element
    If computed is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with matched
        Return 0
    End If
    Let custom_props be proc create from Dict
    If custom_props is equal to 0:
        proc computed_destroy with computed
        proc list_destroy from List with matched
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mcount be proc list_length from List with matched
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than mcount:
        Let m be proc list_get from List with matched, j
        Let pname be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, MATCHED_OFF_NAME
        Let pvalue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, MATCHED_OFF_VALUE
        Let is_custom be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with pname, "--"
        If is_custom is equal to 1:
            proc set from Dict with custom_props, pname, pvalue
        End If
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    Set j to 0
    While j is less than mcount:
        Let mm be proc list_get from List with matched, j
        Let pname2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with mm, MATCHED_OFF_NAME
        Let pvalue2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with mm, MATCHED_OFF_VALUE
        Let is_custom2 be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with pname2, "--"
        If is_custom2 is equal to 0:
            Let resolved be proc cascade_resolve_value with pvalue2, custom_props
            proc computed_set with computed, pname2, resolved
        End If
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    If registry is not equal to 0:
        Let rcount be proc list_length from List with registry
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than rcount:
            Let spec be proc list_get from List with registry, k
            Let pname3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, 0
            Let existing be proc computed_get with computed, pname3
            If existing is equal to 0:
                Let inherited be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, 16
                Let assigned be 0
                If inherited is equal to 1:
                    If parent_computed is not equal to 0:
                        Let parent_val be proc computed_get with parent_computed, pname3
                        If parent_val is not equal to 0:
                            proc computed_set with computed, pname3, parent_val
                            Set assigned to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                If assigned is equal to 0:
                    Let initial be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, 32
                    If initial is not equal to 0:
                        proc computed_set with computed, pname3, initial
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
    End If
    proc destroy from Dict with custom_props
    Let final_count be proc list_length from List with matched
    Let q be 0
    While q is less than final_count:
        Let entry be proc list_get from List with matched, q
        proc matched_destroy with entry
        Set q to q plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with matched
    Return computed
End Process
